title.narrative: CHILD PROTECTION - BEHAVIORAL CHANGE

description.narrative: Boys and girls, parents, teachers and communities have improved awareness of the risks of violence against children and available child protection services., which contributes to Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020 girls and boys are better protected from violence, abuse and exploitation

title.narrative: Boys and girls, parents, teachers and communities have improved awareness of the risks of violence against children and availablechild protection services.

description.narrative: 13,594 boys and girls, parents and community members were equipped with improved awareness of the risks of violence, including gender-based violence and the dangers of mines and other unexploded explosive ordnance, as well as information on access to available child protection services. UNICEF also laid the groundwork for the development of a social behaviour strategy on prevention of and response to violence against children. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:16/01/2022
